Class Rectangle

java.lang.Object
  Drawable
      Rectangle

public class Rectangle
extends Drawable

A Rectangle that can be manipulated and that draws itself on a canvas. Based on the Square class in the original project by Kolling and Barnes.. All values for distances or coordinates on the canvas are in pixels.

Version:
2011/14/09
Author:
Tony Beaumont. Based on code written by Michael Kolling and David J. Barnes

Constructor Detail

Rectangle

public Rectangle()
Constructor for Rectangle objects. New Rectangle objects are all positioned with their top left hand corner at (300,100), have a length of 50 and a height of 30, are coloured red and are initially invisible.

Rectangle

public Rectangle(Integer width,
                 Integer height)
Constructor for Rectangle objects. New Rectangle objects are all positioned with their top left hand corner at (60,50), are coloured red and are initially invisible. Using this constructor the length and height of the rectangle can be provided as parameters at runtime.

Parameters:
length - The initial length of the rectangle
height - The initial height of the rectangle
